<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 6:28PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Phillips and northeastern Petroleum Counties through 730 PM MDT...
At 627 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 22
miles southwest of Fourchette, or 24 miles south of Zortman, moving
northeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central
Phillips and northeastern Petroleum Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
